    <img src="/mbimagespng/poultryraising.png"><span class="maintext">

<h1>Poultry Raising</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Have a knowledge of foster-mothers and the construction of sanitary laying houses, brood coops, and runs.<p>

<li>Understand, through experience - rearing, feeding, caponizing, killing, and dressing birds for the table.<p>

<li>Candle incubating eggs and for the market. Describe the differences in candling, how to distinguish the infertile from the fertile eggs, and the bad from the good eggs; and tell how eggs are graded.<p>

<li>Select good layers and cull the poor producers.<p>

<li>Raise a breed of not less than ten (10) selected pullets.<p>

<center>OR</center></ol><p>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Own a pen of chickens, not less than ten (10) hens and one (1) rooster.<p>

<li>Do all the work in its care and management.<p>

<li>Incubate eggs with the use of brood hens, and raise not less than ten (10) selected pullets for replacement.<p>

<li>Castrate all excess cockerels.<p>

<li>Keep accurate cost accounts record.<p>

<li>Make a complete report at the end of the year as required by your Counselor.</ol>

</span><p>
